# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files that should NEVER end up inside a docker build context.
# Keeping the build context small (a) reduces build time, (b)
# prevents accidentally shipping secrets (.env, *.dump), and (c)
# avoids including the host's git history inside the image.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# VCS metadata
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Build / cache outputs
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
htmlcov/
.coverage

# Local config and secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.log
*.pid

# Docker / infra runtime artefacts
infra/docker/backups/
infra/docker/caddy_data/
infra/docker/caddy_config/
infra/docker/citevyn_pgdata/

# Node / frontend (not built in api / worker images)
node_modules/
.next/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/

# Test / coverage data
tests/
backend/tests/

# Documentation, diagrams, design assets
docs/
diagrams/
*.md
!backend/README.md
# The worker's source corpus ships as package data (#92) — these .md files ARE
# app data the prod worker ingests, not documentation. Docker's ``*.md`` above
# does NOT match nested paths (unlike .gitignore), so they already ship today;
# this explicit re-include documents the intent and future-proofs against a
# broader rule (e.g. ``**/*.md``) that WOULD strip them and break
# ``citevyn-worker run`` in the image.
!backend/app/worker/sources/*.md

# Repo-root files we don't ship inside the image
.claude/
.agents/
.smoke-*
.pytest_cache/
